headline: Analysis: Hims & Hers says its weight-loss business can grow as US market changes
summary: (Reuters) -Hims & Hers Health is betting that the cash-pay market for weight-loss drugs will drive up customer demand although some analysts see a need for the online website to adjust to changing competition in the U.S.  Hims has thrived in the market for cheaper compounded versions of highly in-demand weight-loss drugs, such as Novo Nordisk's Wegovy.  This was allowed by the U.S. Food and Drug Administration when those drugs were in shortage.

headline: PBM lobby sues Arkansas over law requiring drug middlemen to sell pharmacies
summary: The Pharmaceutical Care Management Association is following in the footsteps of two of its largest members — Cigna’s Express Scripts and CVS’ Caremark — that have also sued Arkansas over its controversial law.
